                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/530: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Churchill</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="37" xml:id="d96fn37">Copy forwarded to the Secretary of State by the
                        British Ambassador (Halifax) on April 19.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-18">April 18,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>651. Your 523. Thank you so much. I have told our people to make use of your
                    message to the King and his new Ministers and to read it to mutinous brigade and
                    recalcitrant ships. It may have a most salutary effect. I am not publishing
                    anything here.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
